    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/1wi06b-ei/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=582457335109125081&sectionId=582457335210116057)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggyN_-3QOIM_text","label":"ggyN_-3QOIM_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:40px;\"><strong>Emergency Vet Warns: Fast Water Drinking Creates 30-Minute Death Countdown in Large Breed Dogs</strong></span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggo5om_FqSk_text","label":"ggo5om_FqSk_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:28px;\"><strong>Emergency Vet Warns: Fast Water Drinking Creates 30-Minute Death Countdown in Large Breed Dogs</strong></span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggdGn3gTUFc_text","label":"ggdGn3gTUFc_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(51,51,51);font-size:16px;\"><i>August 25 2025 at 9:17 AM PST</i></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gguJtS_za6C_text","label":"gguJtS_za6C_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(51,51,51);font-size:14px;\"><i>August 25 2025 at 9:17 AM PST</i></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggbePjQG512_text","label":"ggbePjQG512_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgba(255,255,255,0);color:rgb(48,48,48);font-size:18px;\"><i>\"If your dog's stomach flips, you have maybe 30 minutes or she dies. The clock starts ticking the moment they gulp that water.\"</i></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggf0eVLYBd5_text","label":"ggf0eVLYBd5_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:rgba(255,255,255,0);color:rgb(48,48,48);font-size:16px;\">\"If your dog's stomach flips, you have maybe 30 minutes or she dies. The clock starts ticking the moment they gulp that water.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggy20PqEKKi_text","label":"ggy20PqEKKi_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:24px;\"><strong>I thought Max just loved water.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggnYTIMqY-H_text","label":"ggnYTIMqY-H_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>I thought Max just loved water.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6vXvdLMfJ_text","label":"gg6vXvdLMfJ_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">My Golden Retriever would drain her entire bowl in 20 seconds flat. Especially after our evening walks.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">\"She's just eager,\" I told myself. \"Athletic dogs drink fast.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg-9xXgvk1e_text","label":"gg-9xXgvk1e_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">My Golden Retriever would drain her entire bowl in 20 seconds flat. Especially after our evening walks.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"She's just eager,\" I told myself. \"Athletic dogs drink fast.\"</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Turns out I'd been watching a ticking time bomb for three years.</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">If your large breed dog gulps water quickly after exercise...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">If you've ever heard their stomach making gurgling sounds after drinking...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">If you worry about bloat but think you're being \"overprotective\"...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Then what I'm about to share could save your dog's life.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>24% of large breed dogs will experience bloat.</strong> Even WITH emergency surgery, 30% don't survive.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But this isn't the obvious bloat you read about online—the dramatic stomach twisting that happens hours after meals.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>This is the hidden bloat trigger your vet never mentioned.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The \"healthy drinking\" you feel good about is actually creating the perfect storm in your dog's stomach.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggQIij90sMN_text","label":"ggQIij90sMN_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Turns out I'd been watching a ticking time bomb for three years.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg_0Cq1w2bk_text","label":"gg_0Cq1w2bk_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">If your large breed dog gulps water quickly after exercise...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">If you've ever heard their stomach making gurgling sounds after drinking...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">If you worry about bloat but think you're being \"overprotective\"...</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Then what I'm about to share could save your dog's life.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>24% of large breed dogs will experience bloat.</strong> Even WITH emergency surgery, 30% don't survive.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">But this isn't the obvious bloat you read about online—the dramatic stomach twisting that happens hours after meals.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggD4lCia89b_text","label":"ggD4lCia89b_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>This is the hidden bloat trigger your vet never mentioned.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">The \"healthy drinking\" you feel good about is actually creating the perfect storm in your dog's stomach.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg_9gIKZ-vf_text","label":"gg_9gIKZ-vf_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Race Against Time</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggGtzg3Q51p_text","label":"ggGtzg3Q51p_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Race Against Time</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUvvGRqEtC_text","label":"ggUvvGRqEtC_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">My name is Sarah, and I live in Denver with my husband Mike and our 4-year-old Golden, Max.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">I did everything right. Or so I thought.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Max ate slowly from puzzle feeders. No exercise for 2 hours after meals. Premium food in small portions.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">I'd read every bloat prevention article online. Twice.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">But nobody warned me about <strong>water.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">It was a Tuesday night in October. Max had just finished our usual 3-mile hike.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">She bounded straight to her water bowl and—<strong>GULP GULP GULP</strong>—drained the entire thing in maybe 15 seconds.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Within <strong>10 minutes</strong>, her stomach looked different. Bigger. Tight.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gguyRlBiU7E_text","label":"gguyRlBiU7E_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">She started pacing. Then trying to vomit. But only foam came up.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Pink-tinged foam.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">That sound I'll never forget—<strong>HORK HORK HORK</strong>—like she was choking on air.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Mike grabbed the car keys. \"We're going. NOW.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Dr. Rodriguez met us at the emergency entrance. One look at Max's distended stomach and she rushed us straight back.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">\"X-ray immediately. If her stomach has twisted, we're operating in minutes.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">The black bubble on the screen was massive. <strong>Trapped gas filling her entire stomach cavity.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggvknDjvZ0w_text","label":"ggvknDjvZ0w_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">\"She's bloated but hasn't flipped yet. We can decompress with a tube. But Sarah—<strong>this</strong> will happen again.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggv-fE606b__text","label":"ggv-fE606b__text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">My name is Sarah, and I live in Denver with my husband Mike and our 4-year-old Golden, Max.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I did everything right. Or so I thought.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Max ate slowly from puzzle feeders. No exercise for 2 hours after meals. Premium food in small portions.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I'd read every bloat prevention article online. Twice.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But nobody warned me about <strong>water</strong>.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">It was a Tuesday night in October. Max had just finished our usual 3-mile hike.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She bounded straight to her water bowl and—<strong>GULP GULP GULP</strong>—drained the entire thing in maybe 15 seconds.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Within <strong>10 minutes</strong>, her stomach looked different. Bigger. Tight.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPJc-PeDhE_text","label":"ggPJc-PeDhE_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>Max survived. $1,847 later.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggO40BEmS0G_text","label":"ggO40BEmS0G_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She started pacing. Then trying to vomit. But only foam came up.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Pink-tinged foam.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">That sound I'll never forget—<strong>HORK HORK HORK</strong>—like she was choking on air.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Mike grabbed the car keys. \"We're going. NOW.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Dr. Rodriguez met us at the emergency entrance. One look at Max's distended stomach and she rushed us straight back.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"X-ray immediately. If her stomach has twisted, we're operating in minutes.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The black bubble on the screen was massive. <strong>Trapped gas filling her entire stomach cavity.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg9aGxx06Bc_text","label":"gg9aGxx06Bc_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"She's bloated but hasn't flipped yet. We can decompress with a tube. But Sarah—<strong>this</strong> will happen again.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggTnylEUEfq_text","label":"ggTnylEUEfq_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Max survived. $1,847 later.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggoKytRoRSm_text","label":"ggoKytRoRSm_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Shocking Truth Nobody Tells You</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPslHpDfS7_text","label":"ggPslHpDfS7_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Three days later, Dr. Rodriguez called to check on Max.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Sarah, what happened Tuesday wasn't bad luck. It was inevitable.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She explained something that changed everything I thought I knew about bloat.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"Bloat kills more large breed dogs than cancer. But cancer takes months. Bloat takes minutes.\"</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggU-GwWiA-7_text","label":"ggU-GwWiA-7_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She showed me Max's case file. Every previous vet visit, Max's stomach showed signs of chronic gastric irritation.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Look at these notes. 'Mild gastric distension after drinking.' 'Stomach sounds hyperactive post-exercise.' We documented it. But nobody connected the dots.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"But lots of dogs drink fast after exercise—\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"Sarah, 1 in 4 large breed dogs will bloat. 50% mortality rate even with immediate surgery. Max's drinking pattern puts her at maximum risk.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">All those \"precautions\" I'd taken? The slow feeders, the meal timing, the exercise rules?</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>They addressed food bloat. Not water bloat.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"The real problem is gastric shock.\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggAMy63PkuH_text","label":"ggAMy63PkuH_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>Why Everything You've Tried Has Failed</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggHZQmvXCl6_text","label":"ggHZQmvXCl6_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Dr. Rodriguez pulled up a veterinary journal on her tablet.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"When dogs gulp large volumes of cold water rapidly—over 500ml in under 30 seconds—it triggers gastric shock.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Think of jumping into a freezing lake. Your whole body seizes up. <strong>Same thing happens to their stomach.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">The sudden volume combined with temperature shock triggers the vagus nerve to overreact.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Normal stomach contractions stop. Gas builds up. The stomach distends.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>In severe cases, the weight of the distended stomach causes it to flip—GDV.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"According to this European study, traditional prevention methods help food-related bloat by 60%. But they only reduce <strong>water-triggered bloat by 12%.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"The enemy isn't eating too fast. It's <strong>volume shock from drinking too fast.</strong>\"</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggNL5VTPt6l_text","label":"ggNL5VTPt6l_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>The Discovery That Changed Everything</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggloYarTIIr_text","label":"ggloYarTIIr_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Two weeks later, I was obsessing over Max's every drink.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Measuring water portions. Setting timers. Following her around with a stopwatch.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>I was living in terror.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">My neighbor Janet saw me hovering over Max in the backyard.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Sarah, you look exhausted. What's going on?\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I told her about Max's bloat episode. The vet bills. My constant worry.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"Oh honey. I know exactly what you're going through.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Janet had lost her first Golden to bloat five years ago. <strong>$4,200 emergency surgery. He didn't make it.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Her second Golden, Bruno, had <strong>three bloat episodes</strong> before she found what actually works.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Emergency vet in Boulder told me about something that addresses the real problem. It's not about slowing them down. <strong>It's about limiting volume per swallow.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She called Bruno over to demonstrate.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"Watch his water bowl. See how the floating disk only lets small amounts through?\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Bruno pressed the disk down. Water came up slowly through the calibrated holes.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Maybe 30-50ml at a time. The stomach could handle that without shocking.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>\"No shock, no gas buildup, no bloat.\"</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Two years since switching to the </span><a href=\"https://waggier.com/products/waggier-hydrocalm\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><u>Waggier™ HydroCalm</u></span></a><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">. <strong>Zero episodes</strong>.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">\"Bruno used to bloat every 6-8 months. Cost me over $12,000 in emergencies.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">I ordered one that night from my car in Janet's driveway.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggBTEO3jrHK_text","label":"ggBTEO3jrHK_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>Why This Solution Is Different</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggXneSbzlAz_text","label":"ggXneSbzlAz_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">When the </span><a href=\"https://waggier.com/products/waggier-hydrocalm\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong><u>Waggier™ HydroCalm</u></strong></span></a><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"> arrived, I was desperate but skeptical.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Another \"miracle\" bowl claiming to solve everything.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">But Max's reaction was completely different from day one.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">She approached the bowl, pressed the floating disk, water came up slowly through the holes.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\"><strong>Not a gulp. A controlled lap.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:16px;\">Press. Lap. Swallow. <strong>Pause.</strong></span><br><span style=\"ba